<p>Infrastructure costs can also be significantly reduced. Because deployment in many disparate regions is no longer necessary, businesses can access the world's largest gaming market cheaper and easier than ever. Further, OneQode's carrier network engineers handle network-related tasks directly, so companies get world-class network expertise by default.</p>
<h2>Benefits for gamers</h2>
<p>Finally (and most importantly), users can connect from many areas that were previously underserved. For example, gamers on Australia's east coast can now connect to their counterparts in Asia at latencies as low as 63 milliseconds - more than halving the typical latency to Asian servers. This is borne out in many other locations around APAC.</p>
<h2>Open for business</h2>
<p>OneQode's Gaming Hub is open for business now. Several eSports tournaments are also in the works with a league to follow later in the year.</p>
<p>OneQode's international network footprint is also expanding and the team are working hard to connect directly in more locations over the next six months. This will mean latency will continue to drop as new routes come online.
</p>
